  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Air India attack suspect shot dead",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "An alleged terrorist acquitted of the 1985 Air India plane bombings that killed 329 people by detonating a suitcase bomb has been shot dead in Canada.",
        "75-year-old Ripudaman Singh Malik has been killed in a shooting incident in Surrey, British Columbia, Canada. Police said he died on the spot.",
        "A witness told Canada's CBC News that he heard three gunshots and that the victim was bleeding from a neck wound.",
        "Malik, a Sikh businessman who immigrated to Canada in 1972, was one of the suspects accused of bombing an Air India flight bound for London from Toronto and blowing it up off the coast of Ireland.",
        "The incident was recorded as the deadliest terrorist attack in Canada. However, the killers who shot him have not been arrested yet."
      ],
